{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c58fa64c-b685-49cc-a185-cd3ec9e9eb31","content":"Here's the mapping from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform flags:\n\n```sh\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Flag-by-flag translation:**\n\n| VSTest (`dotnet test`) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform | Required package |\n|---|---|---|\n| `--filter \"…\"` | `--filter \"…\"` | *(built-in)* |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` | *(same package)* |\n\nMake sure each test project references the packages above and sets `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` (plus `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` for MSTest) in the `.csproj` so that `dotnet test` delegates to the new platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b578624c-aaeb-42f0-aee4-beb24eac4b8d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling migration, not a codebase task. Let me provide the answer based on my knowledge.\n\nKey differences when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. **Filter syntax**: `--filter` becomes `--filter` still works but the CLI flag format changes. In Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you use `--filter` directly (same syntax).\n\n2. **TRX logger**: `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx` (built-in).\n\n\n3. **Code coverage**: `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` changes to `--coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` when using Microsoft.CodeCoverage.\n4. **Hang and crash dumps**: `--blame-crash` and `--blame-hang` map to `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` respectively, with timeout configuration like `--hangdump-timeout 5m`.\n5. `dotnet test` still works with the new platform when properly configured, though the underlying runner has changed.\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, `dotnet test` functions as a compatibility layer but the native CLI approach is preferred. The filter syntax remains consistent across both approaches, while logger and coverage collection require different flag names and may need additional packages like `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`. I should note that these new command-line options require specific NuGet packages to be installed in the test project for them to work properly.","outputTokens":1160,"requestId":"A036:E8763:C10CC7:E1F275:69FE8696"},"id":"bc584e47-5d08-4288-b019-102fab9b6af4","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:58:18.491Z","parentId":"e86479b8-4b34-4b07-87dd-ff388a53b475"}
